title: Wyoming 28, Nevada 21: Pack falls to winless Cowboys
text:
Wyoming 28, Nevada 21: Pack falls to winless Cowboys AP 4:43 p.m. PDT October 17, 2015 Wyoming receiver Tanner Gentry (4) scores a touchdown past Nevada cornerback Elijah Moody on Saturday at War Memorial Stadium. (Photo: Troy Babbitt/USA TODAY) CONNECT 3 TWEET LINKEDIN 2 COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
LARAMIE, Wyo. — Cam Coffman threw for 213 yards and three touchdowns as Wyoming snapped a nine-game losing streak by beating Nevada, 28-21, on Saturday afternoon. 
Brian Hill rushed for 188 yards for Wyoming (1-6, 1-2 Mountain West), while Coffman completed 18 of 20 attempts. It was the Cowboys’ first win since beating Fresno State 45-17 on Nov. 1, 2014. 
Tyler Stewart completed 25 of 41 attempts for 287 yards and two TDs for Nevada (3-4, 1-2). His 7-yarder to Jerico Richardson drew the Wolf Pack within 28-21 with 6:36 remaining. 
Nevada forced a Wyoming punt but Stewart was sacked by D.J. May on a 4th-and-5 from the Wyoming 36 with 1:36 remaining. 
Wyoming had gone up 28-7 on a 5-yard run by Kellen Overstreet before Stewart’s 12-yard pass to Jerrod Gipson made it 28-14. 
Jacob Hollister, Tanner Gentry and Jake Maulhardt caught TD passes as Wyoming took a 21-7 halftime lead.
